President Biden and President Xi Jinping of China recently held a virtual meeting to discuss the bilateral relationship between their countries. Biden emphasized the need for competition between the US and China to remain peaceful and not escalate into conflict. He called for establishing common ground, being honest about disagreements, and working together on issues like climate change. Biden also highlighted the importance of communication and understanding each other's priorities. President Xi echoed the sentiment, emphasizing the need for China and the US to cooperate, respect each other, and pursue win-win outcomes. He expressed his willingness to work with Biden to advance the interests of both nations and the international community. The meeting covered a wide range of issues, including human rights, economics, and the Indo-Pacific region.